Copy baseline variables to all timepoints for full df

#rename so can use later
names(HEI_Aim2_Long)[names(HEI_Aim2_Long) == 'prnt.empl.bl'] <- 'prnt.empl.b'

#create dataset for table and comparison
baseline_vars <- subset(HEI_Aim2_Long, HEI_Aim2_Long$eventname=="Baseline", select = c("subjectid", "sex", "race_ethnicity", "high.educ", "neighb_phenx_avg_p", "overall.income.b", "prnt.empl.b"))

#rename variables
names(baseline_vars)[names(baseline_vars) == 'sex'] <- 'sex.bl'
names(baseline_vars)[names(baseline_vars) == 'race_ethnicity'] <- 'race_ethnicity.bl'
names(baseline_vars)[names(baseline_vars) == 'high.educ'] <- 'high.educ.bl'
names(baseline_vars)[names(baseline_vars) == 'neighb_phenx_avg_p'] <- 'neighb_phenx_avg_p.bl'
names(baseline_vars)[names(baseline_vars) == 'overall.income.b'] <- 'overall.income.bl'
names(baseline_vars)[names(baseline_vars) == 'prnt.empl.b'] <- 'prnt.empl.bl'

#add to initial df
HEI_Aim2_Long_2 <- merge(HEI_Aim2_Long, baseline_vars, by="subjectid")

Descriptive Table before Cleaning

#factor eventname
HEI_Aim2_Long_2$eventname <- as.factor(HEI_Aim2_Long_2$eventname)
HEI_Aim2_Long_2$eventname <- relevel(HEI_Aim2_Long_2$eventname , ref="Baseline")

#create smaller df
df_prior <- subset(HEI_Aim2_Long_2,select=c("subjectid","abcd_site","eventname","interview_age","reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl","prnt.empl.bl","overall.income.bl","sex.bl","race_ethnicity.bl","high.educ.bl","neighb_phenx_avg_p.bl","cbcl_scr_syn_internal_r","cbcl_scr_syn_external_r","cbcl_scr_syn_anxdep_r","cbcl_scr_syn_withdep_r","cbcl_scr_syn_attention_r","cbcl_scr_syn_rulebreak_r","cbcl_scr_syn_aggressive_r","cbcl_scr_syn_totprob_r"))
#create table
des_table_prior <- tableby(eventname ~ ., data = df_prior[ , -which(names(df_prior) %in% c("subjectid"))], total=F) 
summary(des_table_prior, title = "Descriptive Statistics by Eventname Before Cleaning")

The following variables are time-varying: - all CBCL outcomes - interview_age

df_cc$interview_age.c9 <- df_cc$interview_age-108
#change to years
df_cc$interview_age.c9.y <- df_cc$interview_age.c9/12
#scale pm2.5 by SD
#df_cc$reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.scaled <- scale(df_cc$reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE)
#center pm2.5 to 5 (recommended by WHO)
df_cc$reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5 <- df_cc$reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl-5
#center no2 to 5.33 (recommended by WHO)
df_cc$reshist_addr1_no2_2016_aavg_bl.c533 <- df_cc$reshist_addr1_no2_2016_aavg_bl-5.33

#center around mean
df_cc$neighb_phenx_avg_p.bl.cm <- df_cc$neighb_phenx_avg_p.bl - mean(df_cc$neighb_phenx_avg_p.bl)

#correlation between pm2.5 and no2
cor(df_cc$reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5[df_cc$eventname=="Baseline"], df_cc$reshist_addr1_no2_2016_aavg_bl.c533[df_cc$eventname=="Baseline"], method="pearson")

#calculate the values at 9 and 12 years (centered at 9 yrs) at pm2.5 = 5 & 12 ug/m3 (centered at 5 ug/m3)

#df
internal_prediction_intx <- data.frame(CBCL=c("internal","internal","internal","internal"), Ages=c(0,3,0,3), PM_levels=c(0,0,7,7))

#coefficients
##zi
inter_coef_zi_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r$zi.fit))["(Intercept)"]
pm_coef_zi_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r$zi.fit))["reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"]
age_coef_zi_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r$zi.fit))["interview_age.c9.y"]
intx_coef_zi_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r$zi.fit))["reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5:interview_age.c9.y"]
##count
inter_coef_ct_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r))["(Intercept)"]
pm_coef_ct_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r))["reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"]
age_coef_ct_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r))["interview_age.c9.y"]
intx_coef_ct_internal <- fixef(summary(internal_zinb_r))["reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5:interview_age.c9.y"]

#calculate values
##zi
internal_prediction_intx$zi <- (inter_coef_zi_internal + pm_coef_zi_internal*internal_prediction_intx$PM_levels + age_coef_zi_internal*internal_prediction_intx$Ages + intx_coef_zi_internal*internal_prediction_intx$PM_levels*internal_prediction_intx$Ages)
##count
internal_prediction_intx$count <- (inter_coef_ct_internal + pm_coef_ct_internal*internal_prediction_intx$PM_levels + age_coef_ct_internal*internal_prediction_intx$Ages + intx_coef_ct_internal*internal_prediction_intx$PM_levels*internal_prediction_intx$Ages)

#calculate predictions
internal_prediction_intx$pzero <- exp(internal_prediction_intx$zi) / (1+exp(internal_prediction_intx$zi))
internal_prediction_intx$pcount <- exp(internal_prediction_intx$count) * (1-internal_prediction_intx$pzero)

#calculate differences
##zi
pm5_internal_pzero <- ((internal_prediction_intx[2,6] - internal_prediction_intx[1,6]) / internal_prediction_intx[1,6]) * 100
round(pm5_internal_pzero)
## [1] -13
#13% decrease
pm12_internal_pzero <- ((internal_prediction_intx[4,6] - internal_prediction_intx[3,6]) / internal_prediction_intx[3,6]) * 100
round(pm12_internal_pzero)
## [1] 190
#190% increase
##count
pm5_internal_pcount <- ((internal_prediction_intx[2,7] - internal_prediction_intx[1,7]) / internal_prediction_intx[1,7]) * 100
round(pm5_internal_pcount)
## [1] 9
#9% increase
pm12_internal_pcount <- ((internal_prediction_intx[4,7] - internal_prediction_intx[3,7]) / internal_prediction_intx[3,7]) * 100
round(pm12_internal_pcount)
## [1] -13
#13% decrease

#attention
attention_fdr_main <- as.data.frame(summary(attention_zinb_r_main)$tTable[,1:2])
attention_fdr_main$Pvalue <- summary(attention_zinb_r_main)$tTable[,5]
rownames(attention_fdr_main) <- paste0("attention.", rownames(attention_fdr_main))
#rulebreak
rulebreak_fdr_main <- as.data.frame(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main)$tTable[,1:2])
rulebreak_fdr_main$Pvalue <- summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main)$tTable[,5]
rownames(rulebreak_fdr_main) <- paste0("rulebreak.", rownames(rulebreak_fdr_main))
#aggressive
aggressive_fdr_main <- as.data.frame(summary(aggressive_zinb_r_main)$tTable[,1:2])
aggressive_fdr_main$Pvalue <- summary(aggressive_zinb_r_main)$tTable[,5]
rownames(aggressive_fdr_main) <- paste0("aggressive.", rownames(aggressive_fdr_main))

#all age ("interview_age.c9.y)
age_fdr_main <- rbind(external_fdr_main[c("external.interview_age.c9.y"),],attention_fdr_main[c("attention.interview_age.c9.y"),],rulebreak_fdr_main[c("rulebreak.interview_age.c9.y"),],aggressive_fdr_main[c("aggressive.interview_age.c9.y"),])
age_fdr_main$FDR.corr <- p.adjust(age_fdr_main$Pvalue, method="fdr")
#all pm25 (reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5)
pm25_fdr_main <- rbind(external_fdr_main[c("external.reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"),],attention_fdr_main[c("attention.reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"),],rulebreak_fdr_main[c("rulebreak.reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"),],aggressive_fdr_main[c("aggressive.reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"),])
pm25_fdr_main$FDR.corr <- p.adjust(pm25_fdr_main$Pvalue, method="fdr")

#combine all
all_fdr_main <- rbind(age_fdr_main,pm25_fdr_main)

#calculate the values at 9 and 12 years (centered at 9 yrs) at pm2.5 = 5 & 12 ug/m3 (centered at 5 ug/m3)

#df
rulebreak_prediction_main <- data.frame(CBCL=c("rulebreak","rulebreak"), Ages=c(0,3), PM_levels=c(0,7))

#coefficients
##zi
inter_coef_zi_rulebreak <- fixef(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main$zi.fit))["(Intercept)"]
pm_coef_zi_rulebreak <- fixef(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main$zi.fit))["reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"]
age_coef_zi_rulebreak <- fixef(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main$zi.fit))["interview_age.c9.y"]
##count
inter_coef_ct_rulebreak <- fixef(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main))["(Intercept)"]
pm_coef_ct_rulebreak <- fixef(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main))["reshist_addr1_pm252016aa_bl.c5"]
age_coef_ct_rulebreak <- fixef(summary(rulebreak_zinb_r_main))["interview_age.c9.y"]

#calculate values
##zi
###age
rulebreak_prediction_main$zi_age <- (inter_coef_zi_rulebreak + age_coef_zi_rulebreak*rulebreak_prediction_main$Ages)
###pm2.5
rulebreak_prediction_main$zi_pm <- (inter_coef_zi_rulebreak + pm_coef_zi_rulebreak*rulebreak_prediction_main$PM_levels)
##count
###age
rulebreak_prediction_main$count_age <- (inter_coef_ct_rulebreak + age_coef_ct_rulebreak*rulebreak_prediction_main$Ages)
###pm
rulebreak_prediction_main$count_pm <- (inter_coef_ct_rulebreak + pm_coef_ct_rulebreak*rulebreak_prediction_main$PM_levels)

#calculate predictions
rulebreak_prediction_main$pzero_age <- exp(rulebreak_prediction_main$zi_age) / (1+exp(rulebreak_prediction_main$zi_age))
rulebreak_prediction_main$pzero_pm <- exp(rulebreak_prediction_main$zi_pm) / (1+exp(rulebreak_prediction_main$zi_pm))
rulebreak_prediction_main$pcount_age <- exp(rulebreak_prediction_main$count_age) * (1-rulebreak_prediction_main$pzero_age)
rulebreak_prediction_main$pcount_pm <- exp(rulebreak_prediction_main$count_pm) * (1-rulebreak_prediction_main$pzero_pm)

#calculate differences
##zi
###age

#2% decrease

## [1] -10
#10% decrease
###pm
